Some gifts are just flat out amazing. Like this wallet that my amazing partner got me. She gave it to early for #christmas and I love it. 
I’ve been a #baseball fan my whole life. I played when I was young. Collected cards. Went to minor and major league games. I love the game. So this wallet made from an actual glove is pretty fantastic. It even has that glove smell. If you’re a baseball fan you understand that. 
Thanks Rachel for the cool gift. Check out @fielderschoicegoods for some pretty amazing stuff. #coolestgiftever #happyholidays #loveofthegame

Some people just get you. Like @archiel666 gets me as is obvious in these incredible @deadpoolmovie slippers. What grown man wouldn’t want to walk around in actual #deadpool #bunny slippers? #shegetsme #mustbelove

Stan Lee created worlds and characters that inspired me through out my childhood. I can remember trying to walk on walls as a kid and to this day enjoy reading comics in the morning while drinking coffee. I never met the man but his work has led to friendships created over a mutual love of the mans work. He gave us important characters like @official_captainamerica and @spiderman that had such incredible messages of hope, strength and a desire to do the right thing, even when life got hard. The world will miss the light that he shined upon it. Rest In Peace @therealstanlee you can rest easy knowing you’ve done great works. #excelsior #marvellegends #comicbooknerd #popicon

Here’s to many more years ahead big head dog. #pitbullsofinstagram #dogsofinstagram #mansbestfriend #whataluckymanhewas

Taking #accountability for our actions is important. #life is full of choices. One of the most important is the choice to play the victim role or accept responsibility for the things we’ve done, and then work to #makeamends as best we can. Some may view this list as harsh but there’s a lot of truth in here. I learned so many of these from my father. So much so that as I went through this list I could hear his voice. Especially on number ten. What a life changing idea that was. Life isn’t easy, nor is it fair. We can make it better or worse through any number of things. Hiding in a bottle, whether it’s alcohol or prescription drugs, doesn’t do it. Pushing people away doesn’t do it either. Because in the end you’re still stuck with you. You put yourself here through #actions and #choices made. You can’t possibly get out of it without doing some serious work on yourself. I’m far from perfect in life and am still fully capable of screwing things up. I try to use those times to better myself, to find a way to be a stronger person and a better human being. It’s a long road for sure and each day represents new challenges and opportunities for growth. Trying to take full advantage of those and continue to grow is the goal. Be a good person. Treat others well. Own your actions, good and bad. Do not judge. None of us are perfect. Live, love, and learn. #lifeisbeautiful #learn #recovery #progressnotperfection
